WEBVTT

00:00.501 --> 00:02.935
[ static ]

00:03.137 --> 00:04.470
♪

00:04.472 --> 00:09.341
♪ my dreams are all dead
and buried ♪

00:09.343 --> 00:14.646
♪ sometimes I wish the sun
would just explode ♪

00:14.648 --> 00:19.451
♪ when god comes and calls me
to his kingdom ♪

00:19.453 --> 00:24.856
♪ I'll take all you
sons of bitches when I go ♪

00:24.858 --> 00:27.426
♪ I'll take all you
son of a bitches when I go ♪

00:27.428 --> 00:28.594
my turn.

00:28.596 --> 00:29.995
Hell no.
Hey, man, let me drive

00:29.997 --> 00:31.997
that thing, come on!
Do not touch the trim!

00:35.336 --> 00:37.403
Now, let's all bow
our heads

00:37.405 --> 00:39.571
for a moment of silence.

00:42.410 --> 00:45.394
Hang on. I-I got a late start.
Please don't tell my boss.

00:45.396 --> 00:47.012
Where's the damn
hearse keys?

00:47.014 --> 00:49.898
Some shit-for-brains backed it
up to the wall over there.

00:49.900 --> 00:52.267
That's right, I'm talking
to you, gravedigger.

00:52.269 --> 00:55.187
I thought it'd be easier to get
it out later if I backed it in.

00:55.189 --> 00:56.488
Is that right?

00:56.490 --> 00:58.240
Well, how we gonna
get the coffin out?

00:58.242 --> 01:00.743
Through the sunroof?!

01:00.745 --> 01:02.861
Now, you best have that hole dug
by the time

01:02.863 --> 01:04.329
preacher man says
"amen,"

01:04.331 --> 01:06.582
or I'm gonna snatch
a knot in your skull.

01:06.584 --> 01:08.000
Yes, sir.

01:08.002 --> 01:10.502
Uh-oh, I think I nicked a rock
or something.

01:10.504 --> 01:12.771
Rocks don't make
a hissing sound, stupid!

01:12.773 --> 01:15.424
You busted the gas line
to the crematorium!

01:15.426 --> 01:17.443
Now I gotta relight
the pilot.

01:17.445 --> 01:20.129
Pain in my ass!

01:20.131 --> 01:22.014
Amen, already.
Let's wrap it up.

01:22.016 --> 01:23.766
He's as dead
as he's gonna get!

01:23.768 --> 01:26.602
Ugh!
It's...Hot out here!

01:26.604 --> 01:28.253
Ugh.
Rusty: Excuse me, sir.

01:28.255 --> 01:30.606
Remember when you said that
after I was here a few months,

01:30.608 --> 01:32.641
I could shadow you
while you prep a body?

01:32.643 --> 01:34.359
I just wanna pick
your brain.

01:34.361 --> 01:38.197
Well, I'm pickin' this fella's
brain through his nasal cavity.

01:38.199 --> 01:40.649
Ugh.
Now, they say it's unnecessary,

01:40.651 --> 01:43.068
but 8 pounds is 8 pounds,
and at my age,

01:43.070 --> 01:44.987
I'll do anything
to save my back.

01:44.989 --> 01:46.771
Now, rusty, get
your worthless ass in there

01:46.773 --> 01:47.990
and relight the pilot.

01:47.992 --> 01:49.608
It - it still smells
like gas in here.

01:49.610 --> 01:51.109
Gimme that, goddamn --

01:51.111 --> 01:53.128
always [bleep] gotta have it
your way, goddamn it.

01:53.130 --> 01:55.464
You don't mind if I just crack
the window a little bit, do you?

01:55.466 --> 01:57.049
Yeah, go ahead.

01:57.051 --> 01:59.168
Typical millennial, always
looking for the nearest exit

01:59.170 --> 02:01.086
when there's work
to be done.

02:04.625 --> 02:06.658
Oh!

02:06.660 --> 02:09.311
Aw, damn it,
I was almost outta here.

02:09.313 --> 02:12.364
O-okay, when do y'all wanna
schedule a viewing?

02:12.366 --> 02:15.517
Hell, I don't know, pastor,
I'm just the gravedigger.

02:16.821 --> 02:19.605
It looks like you've
been promoted, rusty.

02:21.025 --> 02:23.975
Ha-ha, look what
the cat dragged in.

02:23.977 --> 02:25.694
Where you been
lollygaggin'?

02:25.696 --> 02:27.112
Some of us have to work,
daddy.

02:27.114 --> 02:28.747
Well, they say
"do what you love,

02:28.749 --> 02:30.649
and you never work a day
in your life."

02:30.651 --> 02:32.167
but I say "don't show up
for work,

02:32.169 --> 02:33.952
and you never work a day
in your life."

02:33.954 --> 02:37.155
and not working has worked
out damn good for me.

02:37.157 --> 02:38.707
I got promoted
from gravedigger

02:38.709 --> 02:40.509
so I'mma need somebody
to fill my old position.

02:40.511 --> 02:41.593
You think you can help?

02:41.595 --> 02:43.045
Mm,
sounds like work to me.

02:43.047 --> 02:44.829
And you know what I say
about work.

02:44.831 --> 02:48.517
It's 10% inspiration,
90% tax evasion,

02:48.519 --> 02:50.602
and 10% ragin' cajun.

02:50.604 --> 02:53.605
Whoo!
I give 110%.

02:53.607 --> 02:54.773
Granny, how about you?

02:54.775 --> 02:56.007
I'll pay you 20 bucks
a hole.

02:56.009 --> 02:58.009
Yeah, any dumbass
can dig a hole!

02:58.011 --> 02:59.611
Hang on,
you can't hire a scab!

02:59.613 --> 03:00.896
Get off me!
She ain't with the union!

03:00.898 --> 03:03.014
This is
a right-to-work state!

03:03.016 --> 03:04.983
Hey guys,
it's the diy funeral guy

03:04.985 --> 03:06.568
with my top 10 embalming hacks.

03:06.570 --> 03:09.154
With a couple of common tools
and some twist ties,

03:09.156 --> 03:11.123
you can do most of
the corpse prep right at home.

03:11.125 --> 03:12.524
Come on, I ain't got all day.
Do something.

03:12.526 --> 03:13.742
Get on with it, boy!

03:13.744 --> 03:16.328
Okay, now we want to make
an incision

03:16.330 --> 03:17.862
right under
the belly button here.

03:17.864 --> 03:19.248
You can see where I shave...

03:19.250 --> 03:20.415
Aw! Ow!
God damn it!

03:20.417 --> 03:22.501
And, uh, you can see
why draining the body

03:22.503 --> 03:23.969
in the last step
was so important.

03:23.971 --> 03:26.972
Otherwise, you'd be covered
in blood right now.

03:26.974 --> 03:29.474
That's $20, that's $20,
that's $20.

03:29.476 --> 03:30.509
I'm gonna be rich!

03:30.511 --> 03:31.810
What in the hell?!

03:31.812 --> 03:33.545
And that school counselor
says to me,

03:33.547 --> 03:35.981
"you're gonna end up
diggin' ditches for a livin'."

03:35.983 --> 03:38.350
my daddy said, "don't you
go gettin' his hopes up.

03:38.352 --> 03:40.185
He ain't got the brains
to go pro."

03:40.187 --> 03:42.771
well, early,
look what I found!

03:42.773 --> 03:44.556
Damn it, woman, I told you
not to dig near

03:44.558 --> 03:46.692
those square rocks
with the scribblings on them!

03:46.694 --> 03:47.892
What in the hell, daddy?!

03:47.894 --> 03:49.894
I said one hole -- one!

03:49.896 --> 03:51.896
You think you're making
a goddamn golf course?!

03:51.898 --> 03:53.532
What are these...
Foxholes?!

03:53.534 --> 03:56.919
I'm trying to run a business,
not dig a...Hole to china.

03:56.921 --> 03:59.204
Well, you said $20 a hole,
so I figured --

03:59.206 --> 04:01.072
you figured you'd just dig
a half a million holes

04:01.074 --> 04:02.708
and charge $20 million?

04:02.710 --> 04:04.075
Uh, sounds good to me.

04:04.077 --> 04:05.510
So, can I invoice that now?

04:05.512 --> 04:08.430
We can fill holes, too,
if you don't like 'em.

04:08.432 --> 04:09.881
For a fair price,
of course.

04:09.883 --> 04:11.516
Bitch, I'll fill this hole
with your body

04:11.518 --> 04:12.935
if you queer
my negotiations!

04:12.937 --> 04:14.353
$20, that's it.

04:14.355 --> 04:16.688
Fill the rest back up.
You heard him.

04:16.690 --> 04:19.107
This is your damn deal.
Awww.

04:19.109 --> 04:21.760
So, uh, who's done run off
to meet his maker?

04:21.762 --> 04:23.028
My asshole boss.

04:23.030 --> 04:24.313
His funeral's gonna be
in 45 minutes,

04:24.315 --> 04:26.898
and I got no idea
what the hell I'm doing!

04:28.569 --> 04:31.153
Hand me
that formaldehyde.

04:34.274 --> 04:35.574
[ burps ] ah.

04:35.576 --> 04:39.294
Formaldehyde-hidee-hoo!

04:39.296 --> 04:41.129
Alright, now,
where's the body?

04:41.131 --> 04:43.165
What in the hell?
Right in front of you, daddy.

04:43.167 --> 04:44.716
Ooh, triplets.

04:44.718 --> 04:46.218
What happened here?

04:46.220 --> 04:47.886
Okay, you don't know
what the hell you're doing.

04:47.888 --> 04:49.972
I know exactly what I'm doing,
okay?

04:49.974 --> 04:51.723
People are just
like animals.

04:51.725 --> 04:54.393
Flesh, bones, teeth, tail,
covered in hair,

04:54.395 --> 04:56.845
multiple stomachs, spend most
of their lives in the forest,

04:56.847 --> 04:58.063
and only live
about seven years.

04:58.065 --> 04:59.681
Daddy, don't cut
his foot off!

04:59.683 --> 05:02.017
Oh, we got us
a armchair undertaker?

05:02.019 --> 05:03.968
Don't you remember that
10-point buck-cycle

05:03.970 --> 05:05.237
I built for you?

05:05.239 --> 05:07.039
I'm doin' it, daddy,
I'm doin' it!

05:07.041 --> 05:09.174
Early: That's right, boy,
hang on to those antler-bars.

05:09.176 --> 05:11.476
Keep your feet on the clavicles,
now!

05:11.478 --> 05:14.696
And don't you remember that
fancy gown I made for granny?

05:14.698 --> 05:17.699
Oh, it's beautiful!

05:17.701 --> 05:19.034
Ahh! Ohh!

05:19.036 --> 05:21.203
Cider vinegar,
to "depungify" the stink.

05:21.205 --> 05:23.005
Now you're ready
for church.

05:23.007 --> 05:25.156
I'm a sumbitchin'
roadkill rembrandt!

05:25.158 --> 05:27.342
You just go on and show
them folks where to sit.

05:27.344 --> 05:28.627
I'll provide the show.

05:28.629 --> 05:30.712
Now, let's get to work!

05:31.799 --> 05:34.850
Whoo!
We got 300 graves to fill!

05:36.020 --> 05:38.169
Rusty: This here
is my first eulogy.

05:38.171 --> 05:39.388
I usually
just dig the holes,

05:39.390 --> 05:42.140
but I can tell by this crowd
how much

05:42.142 --> 05:44.026
bubba was loved
in this community.

05:44.028 --> 05:46.111
Is that a joke,
gravedigger?

05:46.113 --> 05:49.698
How 'bout you stop vamping,
'cause it's not about you!

05:49.700 --> 05:50.849
Come on, daddy, chop-chop!

05:50.851 --> 05:52.868
They're gettin' restless
out here!

05:52.870 --> 05:55.871
[ singing "circle of life"
in zulu ]

05:55.873 --> 05:59.624
♪

05:59.626 --> 06:01.192
mele "kamikilaka"!

06:01.194 --> 06:04.296
That's hawaiian for
"welcome to the great beyond!"

06:04.298 --> 06:07.532
♪

06:07.534 --> 06:08.700
rusty: Oh, no.
Whoo!

06:08.702 --> 06:10.202
No, daddy!
Come on, y'all!

06:10.204 --> 06:11.536
Everybody gets lei'd!
[laid]

06:11.538 --> 06:13.755
I can't believe it!
I'm so sorry, everybody.

06:13.757 --> 06:15.474
I-I'll make this right,
I promise.

06:15.476 --> 06:18.143
Bubba always wanted to be
the life of the party.

06:18.145 --> 06:20.645
Yeah, I went full
parrot head on bubba.

06:20.647 --> 06:24.215
And wait
till you see this!

06:24.217 --> 06:28.019
I hollowed out his pelvis and
jammed a paint mixer up his ass.

06:28.021 --> 06:29.938
What have you done?
I love it.

06:29.940 --> 06:31.289
It's so fun.

06:31.291 --> 06:33.024
Now let's all head
over to the gravesite

06:33.026 --> 06:34.826
for a pig-pickin' luau.

06:34.828 --> 06:37.963
Whoo!

06:37.965 --> 06:40.165
Rest in pork, my friend.

06:41.135 --> 06:42.834
May you rest in pork.

06:42.836 --> 06:45.137
I am surprised to say this,
but, hell,

06:45.139 --> 06:48.290
I think we got us
a business model here.

06:48.292 --> 06:50.959
Suicide
was always a tragedy.

06:50.961 --> 06:53.095
But I was able to repurpose
the noose

06:53.097 --> 06:54.930
and flip the script
on this.

06:54.932 --> 06:57.933
He's filled with candy hearts
that say the things in death

06:57.935 --> 06:59.918
that he could never
express in life.

06:59.920 --> 07:01.386
No, no, no,
don't eat that!

07:01.388 --> 07:03.088
Muy malo!

07:05.125 --> 07:07.776
Granny: Sign up
for your cuyler original!

07:07.778 --> 07:09.728
Sorry for your loss.
No pushin'!

07:09.730 --> 07:11.696
Single file, please!

07:11.698 --> 07:15.901
The one thing my husband
truly loved was auburn football.

07:15.903 --> 07:17.402
Oh, auburn, huh?

07:17.404 --> 07:21.123
We were hopin' maybe you could
pay tribute to that.

07:21.125 --> 07:24.275
So, you're pretty much fixed
on auburn, huh?

07:24.277 --> 07:27.662
No, no. No, sir!
Hell, no!

07:27.664 --> 07:29.113
Point me to the loved ones.

07:29.115 --> 07:30.966
No, no, just stop it daddy.
I'll talk to 'em.

07:30.968 --> 07:33.084
Hey, folks, listen,
I'm sorry,

07:33.086 --> 07:36.338
but I don't think we can
accommodate your kind here.

07:36.340 --> 07:37.172
What? Wait.

07:37.174 --> 07:38.673
What "kind" is that,
early?

07:38.675 --> 07:40.842
I think we all know
what I'm talkin' about, glenn.

07:40.844 --> 07:44.312
You know, she came all the way
from alabama on my referral.

07:44.314 --> 07:47.432
I'm sorry, but he can't be
buried at a georgia graveyard.

07:47.434 --> 07:49.434
The red georgia clay
will reject him.

07:49.436 --> 07:51.302
It's red
for a damn reason!

07:51.304 --> 07:52.971
Georgia bulldogs, baby!
Sic 'em!

07:52.973 --> 07:54.439
Woof, woof, woof, woof!
Woof, woof!

07:54.441 --> 07:56.741
But -- but I am sure my
colleague can make an exception.

07:56.743 --> 07:58.276
Ain't that right, daddy?

07:58.278 --> 08:01.196
If it was an inferior
acc team -- say, georgia tech

08:01.198 --> 08:03.782
or wake forest --
I'd do that out of sympathy.

08:03.784 --> 08:05.450
But auburn?
I refuse!

08:05.452 --> 08:06.918
Daddy,
this is your job,

08:06.920 --> 08:08.086
so unless you want me
to fire your ass,

08:08.088 --> 08:09.487
I suggest you do
what I say.

08:09.489 --> 08:11.673
Well, I suggest they take
his auburn-lovin' ass

08:11.675 --> 08:14.042
down the street
to another establishment --

08:14.044 --> 08:16.127
one where they don't care
who they mingle with!

08:16.129 --> 08:17.462
Get out!
Security!

08:17.464 --> 08:18.997
Alright, early, alright!
Fine!

08:18.999 --> 08:20.465
I would say,
"sorry for your loss,"

08:20.467 --> 08:22.517
but you're so damn used
to losing to georgia,

08:22.519 --> 08:24.719
I'd be apologizin'
you nonstop!

08:24.721 --> 08:26.137
Come on.

08:26.139 --> 08:28.273
I apologize, folks.
I can prepare the body.

08:28.275 --> 08:29.558
It's auburn tigers,
right?

08:29.560 --> 08:32.010
That's right.
War damn eagle.

08:32.012 --> 08:34.813
Wait -- wait a minute, so,
there's an eagle, too?

08:34.815 --> 08:36.314
[ telephone rings ]

08:36.316 --> 08:38.617
jiggle hut. If you're callin'
about a prostitute,

08:38.619 --> 08:39.684
we don't do that anymore.

08:39.686 --> 08:41.219
[ chuckles ] wink, wink.

08:41.221 --> 08:44.322
Hey, ellis. Uh, listen here,
you still trafficking them,

08:44.324 --> 08:46.491
uh, exotic animals
and whatnot?

08:46.493 --> 08:49.961
Officially, the petting zoo
is closed due to lack of permit,

08:49.963 --> 08:53.231
but we could still do
"private events"

08:53.233 --> 08:54.666
if the money is right.

08:54.668 --> 08:56.218
<i> Yeah, man, I got money.</i>
<i> Let's talk turkey.</i>

08:56.220 --> 08:58.136
Oh, good, cause that's really
all I have left,

08:58.138 --> 08:59.754
mostly, is turkeys.
[ turkeys gobbling ]

08:59.756 --> 09:02.807
now, you ain't goin' over
the state line, are ya?

09:02.809 --> 09:04.226
Ma'am,
I think we put together

09:04.228 --> 09:06.761
a very moving tribute
to your husband.

09:06.763 --> 09:09.431
Yeah, it's movin' a lot,
so, uh, let's pick up the pace.

09:09.433 --> 09:10.815
He's smellin' the meat.
Is --

09:10.817 --> 09:12.267
are those live animals
in there?

09:12.269 --> 09:13.768
Yeah,
but they're sedated.

09:13.770 --> 09:15.437
Right, ellis?
Oh, yeah.

09:15.439 --> 09:16.855
Heavily sedated.

09:16.857 --> 09:18.222
Yeah, I ain't doing this.

09:18.224 --> 09:20.358
Here, I highlighted
the relevant passages.

09:20.360 --> 09:23.028
You can just wing it.
Nobody listens anyway.

09:23.030 --> 09:24.496
Down! Down!

09:24.498 --> 09:28.500
Uh, [clears throat]
will everyone please be seated?

09:28.502 --> 09:31.336
We're gathered here today
in the presence of god

09:31.338 --> 09:33.004
to honor the life of --
[ airhorn blows ]

09:33.006 --> 09:35.674
how dare you invoke
the name of god,

09:35.676 --> 09:38.076
preparing a auburn body
for burial!

09:38.078 --> 09:40.045
God hates auburn!

09:40.047 --> 09:41.263
Oh, daddy, no!

09:41.265 --> 09:43.247
Oh, hell, he's gone
full westboro.

09:43.249 --> 09:47.085
Behold, the mark of the beast --
the "au" on the helmet!

09:47.087 --> 09:50.021
Folks, y'all don't
listen to this!
[ airhorn blows ]

09:50.023 --> 09:52.590
apple ceo tim apple
went to auburn,

09:52.592 --> 09:56.778
and now we all have government
tracking chips in our heads.

09:56.780 --> 09:58.146
Daddy,
keep it down, now.

09:58.148 --> 10:00.031
You're rilin' up the tiger!
Wait, hold up.

10:00.033 --> 10:01.449
You got a living tiger?

10:01.451 --> 10:03.318
Yeah, I couldn't scrape up
an eagle in time,

10:03.320 --> 10:06.871
but I think
the wild turkey works.

10:06.873 --> 10:08.439
Oh, god.

10:08.441 --> 10:11.543
Thou shall not worship
two mascots!

10:13.630 --> 10:15.630
Oh, lindsey!

10:15.632 --> 10:17.415
Uh, I gotta jet.

10:17.417 --> 10:19.167
Stay calm,
everybody, stay calm!

10:19.169 --> 10:20.635
They --
they can smell fear.

10:20.637 --> 10:22.087
[ growls ]

10:22.089 --> 10:23.638
please, early, help!

10:23.640 --> 10:25.140
Hell, no!
Oh!

10:25.142 --> 10:26.591
Get down, tiger!
It's got my leg, early!

10:26.593 --> 10:28.426
Ha, ha, ha!
Ya damn auburn-lover!

10:28.428 --> 10:29.978
Damn it,
and I liked this job.

10:29.980 --> 10:32.463
That's what you get
when you take on the dawgs!

10:32.465 --> 10:34.766
Sic 'em! Woof, woof, woof, woof!
Woof, woof, woof, woof!

10:34.768 --> 10:43.108
♪

10:43.110 --> 10:51.616
♪

10:51.618 --> 10:56.688
♪
